docs.abstract: The company, Haven, had promised to disrupt the way large corporations deliver benefits to their employees.
docs.snippet: The company, Haven, had promised to disrupt the way large corporations deliver benefits to their employees.
docs.lead_paragraph: A joint venture formed by Amazon, Berkshire Hathaway and JPMorgan Chase to explore new ways to deliver health care to their employees is disbanding, according to a short statement on its website. The company, Haven, will cease operations at the end of February — three years after its arrival sent shock waves through the health care industry.

headline.main: Amazon, Berkshire and JPMorgan Will End Joint Health Care Venture
headline.print_headline: Bold Health Care Venture Comes to a Quiet Ending

docs.abstract: Deplatforming President Trump showed that the First Amendment is broken — but not in the way his supporters think.
docs.snippet: Deplatforming President Trump showed that the First Amendment is broken — but not in the way his supporters think.
docs.lead_paragraph: In the months leading up to the November election, the social media platform Parler attracted millions of new users by promising something competitors, increasingly, did not: unfettered free speech. “If you can say it on the streets of New York,” promised the company’s chief executive, John Matze, in a June CNBC interview, “you can say it on Parler.”

headline.main: Why Is Big Tech Policing Speech? Because the Government Isn’t

docs.abstract: Social media platforms have raced to bar organizers of the attack on the Capitol. Will that make a repeat less likely, or just harder to prevent?
docs.snippet: Social media platforms have raced to bar organizers of the attack on the Capitol. Will that make a repeat less likely, or just harder to prevent?
docs.lead_paragraph: After the attack on the Capitol, social media platforms sprang into action. On Facebook and Twitter, accounts — including President Trump’s — were suspended and the pages of whole groups were taken down. Parler, a fringe platform that had become popular among Trump fans, was pulled by Amazon.
